        .section_header.alert.alert-warning.my-4
          #changes
          |                 Configuration Overview
        .content_section_text
          p
            | Debian's Apache2 default configuration is different from the upstream default configuration, and split into several files optimized for interaction with Debian tools. The configuration system is
            b
              | fully documented in
              | /usr/share/doc/apache2/README.Debian.gz
            | . Refer to this for the full documentation. Documentation for the web server itself can be found by accessing the 
            a(href='/manual') manual
            |  if the 
            tt apache2-doc
            |  package
            |                     was installed on this server.
          p
            | The configuration layout for an Apache2 web server installation on Debian systems is as follows:
          code
            p
              | /etc/apache2/
              br
              |                         |-- apache2.conf
              br
              |                         |       `--  ports.conf
              br
              |                         |-- mods-enabled
              br
              |                         |       |-- *.load
              br
              |                         |       `-- *.conf
              br
              |                         |-- conf-enabled
              br
              |                         |       `-- *.conf
              br
              |                         |-- sites-enabled
              br
              |                         |       `-- *.conf
              br
          ul
            li
              tt apache2.conf
              |  is the main configuration file. It puts the pieces together by including all remaining configuration files when starting up the web server.
            li
              tt ports.conf
              |  is always included from the main configuration file. It is used to determine the listening ports for incoming connections, and this file can be customized anytime.
            li
              | Configuration files in the 
              tt mods-enabled/
              | ,
              tt conf-enabled/
              |  and 
              tt sites-enabled/
              |  directories contain particular configuration snippets which manage modules, global configuration fragments, or virtual host configurations, respectively.
            li
              | They are activated by symlinking available configuration files from their respective *-available/ counterparts. These should be managed by using our helpers
              tt
                | a2enmod,
                | a2dismod,
              tt
                | a2ensite,
                | a2dissite,
              |  and
              tt
                | a2enconf,
                | a2disconf
              | . See their respective man pages for detailed information.
            li
              | The binary is called apache2. Due to the use of environment variables, in the default configuration, apache2 needs to be started/stopped with 
              tt /etc/init.d/apache2
              |  or 
              tt apache2ctl
              | .
              b
                | Calling 
                tt /usr/bin/apache2
                |  directly will not work
              |  with the default configuration.
        .section_header.alert.alert-primary.my-4
