            | By default, Debian does not allow access through the web browser to
            em any
            |  file apart of those located in 
            tt /var/www
            | ,
            a(href='http://httpd.apache.org/docs/2.4/mod/mod_userdir.html', rel='nofollow') public_html
            |  directories (when enabled) and 
            tt /usr/share
            |  (for web applications). If your site is using a web document root located elsewhere (such
            |                     as in 
            tt /srv
            | ) you may need to whitelist your document root directory in 
            tt /etc/apache2/apache2.conf
            | .
          p
            | The default Debian document root is 
            tt /var/www/html
            | . You can make your own virtual hosts under /var/www. This is different to previous releases which provides better security out of the box.
